<p>Approximately one in five teens has at least one mental health disorder.  About 1 in 4 of American adults develops a diagnosable mental disorder in a given year.  Individuals with mental illness often develop a substance use disorder when learning how to cope.</p>

<p>Only a professional can diagnose a person with a mental illness because each condition is unique, but there are Common Warning Signs and Symptoms to look for.</p>

<p>A good first step is to TALK TO SOMEONE.   Remember, We All Have Mental Health.  Call your County’s “warm line” for LIVE support and resource information:</p>

